<h2 id=3D"MacOSSetup-CommonSoftwareInstallation">Common Software Installati=
on</h2>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-OnceloggedviaCitrixSecureAccess(VPN)intoMAC"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Once logged via Citrix Secure Access (VPN) int=
o MAC</span></h3>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Open Westpac "Self Service" App</=
span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Browse "Developer" and install&nb=
sp;</span>&nbsp;=20
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Xcode -&nbsp;This will download a=
nd install a lot of command line tools that we'll need.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Homebrew</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Amazon Corretto 21 JDK (if develo=
ping Java code)</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Visual Studio Code or IntelliJ ID=
EA CE</span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Source Tree</span></li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Download Postman (old version) fr=
om here <a href=3D"https://community.postman.com/t/direct-download-link-for=
-9-x/29148" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://community.post=
man.com/t/direct-download-link-for-9-x/29148</a></span></li>
</ol>
<h3 style=3D"text-align: left;" id=3D"MacOSSetup-Proxyworkaround">Proxy wor=
k around&nbsp;</h3>
<p>To ensure that the right proxies are being applied, follow the steps bel=
ow.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>NOTE: This may cause npm installations that use node-gyp and can=
vas to fail. If so, refer to the known issues section.</strong></p>
<p><strong>For &gt;M1 Macs:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Update or create ~/.zshrc file</li>
<li><p>Add the following proxy setting&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Emacs" data-theme=3D"Emacs">httpProxyServer=
=3Dhttp://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080
httpsProxyServer=3Dhttp://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080

export http_proxy=3D$httpProxyServer
export https_proxy=3D$httpsProxyServer
export HTTP_PROXY=3D$httpProxyServer
export HTTPS_PROXY=3D$httpsProxyServer
export no_proxy=3Dsrv.westpac.com.au,schema.wdpconnect.westpac.com.au,home,=
localhost,127.0.0.*
export NO_PROXY=3Dsrv.westpac.com.au,schema.wdpconnect.westpac.com.au,home,=
localhost,127.0.0.*
</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ol>
<p><strong>For older Macs</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Update or create ~/.bash_profile file</li>
<li><p>Add the following proxy setting&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Emacs" data-theme=3D"Emacs">httpProxyServer=
=3Dhttp://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080
httpsProxyServer=3Dhttp://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080

export http_proxy=3D$httpProxyServer
export https_proxy=3D$httpsProxyServer
export HTTP_PROXY=3D$httpProxyServer
export HTTPS_PROXY=3D$httpsProxyServer
export no_proxy=3Dsrv.westpac.com.au,schema.wdpconnect.westpac.com.au,home,=
localhost,127.0.0.*
export NO_PROXY=3Dsrv.westpac.com.au,schema.wdpconnect.westpac.com.au,home,=
localhost,127.0.0.*
</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Add to your ~/.zshrc file (this assumes you have migrated your mac t=
erminal to zsh)</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Emacs" data-theme=3D"Emacs">if [ -f ~/.bash_p=
rofile ]; then . ~/.bash_profile; fi</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>Restart your terminal</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-SetupNode"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Setup=
 Node</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Install nodejs via Brew or NVM</sp=
an></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">brew instal=
l node@22</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">and then follow the following guid=
e:</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><a href=3D"/display/MESH/2.2+Node.=
js+installation+and+setup">2.2 Node.js installation and setup</a></span></p=
>
<h3 style=3D"text-align: left;" id=3D"MacOSSetup-SetupGIT">Setup GIT</h3>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Preferably, install <u>Xcode CLT Selector</u=
> from the <u>Self Service</u> App and that will get you git. You can also =
simply execute the following command in your terminal and you will be promp=
ted to install Xcode tools.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">git</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Configuration of git is not different on a m=
ac than on Windows.</p>
<h3 style=3D"text-align: left;" id=3D"MacOSSetup-MESHDevTools">MESH Dev Too=
ls</h3>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This r=
equires brew to be installed</span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Install python, once installation is complet=
e verify the path where the package is installed:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">brew instal=
l python@3.11
which python3.11</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">ln -s $HOME=
BREW_PREFIX/bin/python3.11 $HOMEBREW_PREFIX/bin/python
ln -s $HOMEBREW_PREFIX/bin/pip3.11 $HOMEBREW_PREFIX/bin/pip</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>If your python3.11 and pip3.11 files are installed somewhere else then y=
ou are on your own.</p>
<p>Execute the following commands to configure pip</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">pip config =
set global.index-url https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifactory/api=
/pypi/westpac-pypi/simple
pip config set global.index https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifact=
ory/api/pypi/westpac-pypi/simple
pip config set global.trusted-host artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au
mkdir -p ~/.config/certs/
curl -Ss https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/wdp-confi=
g-mgmt-ansible-inventory/raw/all/files/client_trusted_chain.pem -o ~/.confi=
g/certs/client_trusted_chain.pem
pip config set global.cert ~/.config/certs/client_trusted_chain.pem</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Proceed with installation following the commands below:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">brew instal=
l openssl rust
pip install cryptography
pip install mesh-dev-tools</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"MacOSSetup-OptionalSoftwareInstallation">Optional Software Instal=
lation</h2>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-NVM">NVM</h3>
<p>This requires brew to be installed</p>
<ol>
<li>run the following command in terminal<br>
 $ brew install nvm</li>
<li>Modify your .zshrc file to map nvm<br>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">export NVM_=
DIR=3D"$HOME/.nvm"
  [ -s "/opt/homebrew/opt/nvm/nvm.sh" ] &amp;&amp; \. "/opt/homebrew/opt/nv=
m/nvm.sh"  # This loads nvm
  [ -s "/opt/homebrew/opt/nvm/etc/bash_completion.d/nvm" ] &amp;&amp; \. "/=
opt/homebrew/opt/nvm/etc/bash_completion.d/nvm"  # This loads nvm bash_comp=
letion


export NVM_CURRENT=3D"~/.nvm/versions/node/$(nvm current)/"</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>install LTS versions of Node (install node 22 as default)</li>
<li>If you are install older versions of Node (14) on a newer Silicon Mac (=
arm64) you will need to switch your terminal architecture to x64, before tr=
ying to nvm install. This is because there is no arm64 version of the node =
14 binary&nbsp; &nbsp;=20
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">arch -x86_6=
4 zsh
nvm install 14</pre>
</div>
</div><a href=3D"https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm/issues/3148#issuecomment-213=
4442775" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://github.com/nvm-sh=
/nvm/issues/3148#issuecomment-2134442775</a>&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
<p><u>Troubleshooting&nbsp; &lt; v16 Node versions on MacOS</u></p>
<ul>
<li>If you are installing a version of node lower than 16 using an M1 Mac, =
nvm may download and compile your node runtime using experimental arm64 bin=
aries. This may cause errors in your local installs/builds as node will att=
empt to install arm64 versions of packages which our internal artifactory m=
ay not have. This is the case with <strong>Canvas@2.6.1</strong>. If you ru=
n into this issue, see&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm#macos-=
troubleshooting" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://github.co=
m/nvm-sh/nvm#macos-troubleshooting</a>&nbsp;&gt; Macs with M1 Chip and foll=
ow the steps to get an x64 version of node installed via nvm&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-Setupprinter">Set up printer</h3>
<p>See:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://sm2.sn.westpac.com.au/msp?id=3Dkb_article&a=
mp;table=3Dkb_knowledge&amp;sys_kb_id=3D8c229c1ec3802614ca28751ed4013157&am=
p;searchTerm=3Dsetting%20up%20printer%20on%20a%20Mac" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">Self-Help Portal - Internal Customer - Apple Mac - Sett=
ing up printer on a MacBook</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-JDK/Maven">JDK / Maven</h3>
<p>JDK: Open the Self Service app, under Developer (or use search) install =
Amazon Corretto 21</p>
<p>Maven:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">brew instal=
l maven</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Alternatively you can install Maven manually by following this link</p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/MD/How+to+install+Maven+without+admin+rights+on+your=
+macbook">How to install Maven without admin rights on your macbook</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-IDEs">IDEs</h3>
<h4 id=3D"MacOSSetup-General">General</h4>
<p>For IDEs like PyCharm, IntelliJ and Visual Studio Code, download the Mac=
 compatible binary (Apple Silicon for M1 Macs) and copy to <strong>YOUR App=
lication folder</strong>. Open Finder, Go to folder.., Macintosh HD =E2=86=
=92&nbsp;&lt;your salary id&gt;&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Applications.</p>
<p>You can have a look at this article on how to install apps to your user =
directory.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/MD/How+to+install+apps+%28e.g.+WebStorm%29+without+a=
dmin+access+on+your+Macbook">How to install apps (e.g. WebStorm) without ad=
min access on your Macbook</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"MacOSSetup-IntelliJ">IntelliJ</h4>
<p>Make sure you got Java and Maven installed and set:</p>
<p>Maven:</p>
<ul>
<li>Maven home path as&nbsp;/Users/&lt;your user account&gt;/.homebrew/Cell=
ar/maven/3.8.6/libexec</li>
<li>User settings file as&nbsp;/Users/&lt;your user account&gt;/.m2/setting=
s.xml</li>
<li>Local repository as&nbsp;/Users/&lt;your user account&gt;/.m2/repositor=
y</li>
<li>Tick the "Use settings from .mvn/maven.config" option</li>
</ul>
<p>JDK: if you are only using JDK 21 as above you should be OK, just make s=
ure that:</p>
<ul>
<li>On File&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Project Settings=20
<ul>
<li>SDK: you have correto-21</li>
<li>Project: correto-21</li>
</ul></li>
<li>On IntelliJ IDEA&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Preferences...&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Maven=20
<ul>
<li>Importing: JDK for importer is properly set as Project SDK</li>
<li>Runner: JRE is&nbsp;properly set as Project SDK</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>You can find a slightly more detailed overview on how to setup your macb=
ook in the article below.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/MD/How+to+setup+your+MacBook+without+admin+access">H=
ow to setup your MacBook without admin access</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacOSSetup-KnownIssues">Known Issues</h2>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-IssuerCertificateNodeGyp/CanvasInstallationIssues">Iss=
uer Certificate Node Gyp / Canvas Installation Issues</h3>
<p>If you are experiencing issuer certificate errors when running an <code>=
npm install</code> , this is most likely caused by any HTTP Proxy setup thr=
ough your bash_profile or zshrc (whichever you used to define the proxies).=
 To resolve, you can remove the lines from the <code>.bash_profile</code> o=
r <code>.zshrc</code>&nbsp;and restart your terminal. (note: after restarti=
ng, verify that the terminal has unbound the proxies by typing <code>echo $=
http_proxy</code>&nbsp; and verify that nothing prints below it)</p>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-AccesstoPeopleExpressthrowsxmlerrorbothedgeandchrome">=
Access to People Express throws xml error both edge and chrome</h3>
<p>See: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://sm2.sn.westpac.com.au/wb=
gtechserviceportal?sys_kb_id=3D84ca1ee48765695051e521b8dabb35db&amp;id=3Dkb=
_article_view&amp;sysparm_rank=3D1&amp;sysparm_tsqueryId=3D4fca07491b11b114=
269edce8b04bcbca" rel=3D"nofollow">https://sm2.sn.westpac.com.au/wbgtechser=
viceportal?sys_kb_id=3D84ca1ee48765695051e521b8dabb35db&amp;id=3Dkb_article=
_view&amp;sysparm_rank=3D1&amp;sysparm_tsqueryId=3D4fca07491b11b114269edce8=
b04bcbca</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"MacOSSetup-IncorrectMSTeamsstatus">Incorrect MS Teams status</h3>
<p>If you have issues with Teams not updating it's status, make sure to upd=
ate Office 365 to the latest version by:</p>
<ol>
<li><p class=3D"p1">Open Microsoft Word or any other MS Office Suite applic=
ation other than Teams</p></li>
<li><p class=3D"p1">Select the Check for updates under the help menu</p></l=
i>
<li><p class=3D"p1">Select Microsoft auto update option and proceed (you ne=
ed to close Microsoft applications so they can be updated)</p></li>
</ol>
<p>If the above does not work:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Quit Teams app and Login to <a href=3D"http://portal.office.com" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">portal.office.com</a> using browser</=
p></li>
<li><p>Click of Teams and see if your Status changes when using web</p></li=
>
<li><p>Reset Microsoft Teams setting to default</p></li>
<li><p>Quit Microsoft Teams and launch Self Service app. Under Utilities -&=
gt; "Reset Microsoft Teams</p></li>
<li><p>Re-launch Teams and test</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"MacOSSetup-OfficialKnowledgeBase">Official Knowledge Base</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://sm2.sn.westpac.com.au/wbgtechserviceportal?id=3Dsearc=
h&amp;spa=3D1&amp;q=3DApple%20Mac" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>https://sm2.sn.westpac.com.au/wbgtechserviceportal?id=3Dsearch&amp;spa=3D1=
&amp;q=3DApple%20Mac</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
